4 HR____ MOURNING THE DEATH AND CELEBRATING THE LIFE OF
5 PHILLIP EDWARD HINKLE.
6
7 WHEREAS, it is with profound sorrow that we note the
8 death of Phillip Edward "Phil" Hinkle of Homewood, Alabama,
9 on March 10, 2026, at the age of 84; and
10 WHEREAS, his departure leaves a void in the lives of
11 his loving family, many friends, and the community where he
12 was highly regarded; and
13 WHEREAS, Phil Hinkle was born on July 3, 1941, in
14 Birmingham, Alabama to Francis Hunter Hinkle and Edine
15 Tucker Hinkle and grew up in Birmingham; he graduated from
16 Woodlawn High School and attended The University of Alabama
17 and Howard College, now Samford University; and
18 WHEREAS, in 1964, Phil joined the family business,
19 Hinkle Supply, which was founded in 1926; he later joined
20 with his brother, Francis Hinkle, to open Hinkle Metal and
21 Supply in 1980, distributing heating and air conditioning
22 products in the Southeast; and
23 WHEREAS, Phil was more than a hard worker; he was
24 also an avid sportsman; he enjoyed all outdoor sports,
25 particularly fishing and hunting, and was a member of the
26 Henley Hunting Club in Geiger, Alabama, for 40 years; he and
27 his family also enjoyed relaxing at Old Overton Country
28 Club, where he loved playing golf and the 19th hole; and
Page 1

Club, where he loved playing golf and the 19th hole; and
HR258 INTRODUCED
29 WHEREAS, Phil was preceded in death by his son,
30 Justin Bradley Hinkle, and his parents; he is survived by
31 his loving wife, Carol Ann Fuller Hinkle; children, Austin
32 Merritt Hinkle (Hope) and Leigh Ann Hinkle Barker (Chad);
33 daughter-in-law, Melissa Barton Hinkle; grandchildren, Ella
34 Grace Barker, Chole Annabelle Barker, Dexter August Barker,
35 Connor Joseph Hinkle, and Marin Grace Hinkle; faithful
36 canine companions, Trump and Precious; many nieces and
37 nephews; and a host of other family and friends; now
38 therefore,
39 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
40 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That the death of Phillip Edward
41 "Phil" Hinkle is recorded with deep sadness, and even as we
42 mourn his death and the loss it represents, we also
43 celebrate his life; this resolution is offered in highest
44 tribute, along with heartfelt sympathy to his family, whose
45 grief is shared by many.
